    <section id="products">
      <h2>4. Products &amp; Services</h2>
      <p><strong>What they sell:</strong> Exclusive, real-time auto-accident lead generation for PI attorneys (and PI doctors). Proprietary system uses custom client-branded landing pages; accident victims submit accident date, contact details, location and a representation-interest question; qualifying leads are forwarded immediately. Built-in follow-up sequences re-engage initially uninterested prospects.</p>
      <p><strong>Pricing model:</strong> Flat monthly retainer by territory — ~$2,500 per million people targeted; a 3M-population region runs ~$7,500/month, billed upfront. Recurring, territorially-exclusive subscription model.</p>
      <p><strong>Differentiators:</strong> Proprietary accident-report search methodology; 8+ years of accident data; claimed lower cost-per-closed-lead vs. traditional PPC; geographic exclusivity; positioned as dominant in the accident-report-search niche.</p>
    </section>

    <section id="market">
      <h2>5. Market Analysis</h2>
      <p><strong>Industry size and trends:</strong> US PI legal market ~$61.7B in 2025 (IBISWorld), ~2.5% CAGR. PI advertising spend exceeded $2.5B in 2024; PI leads carry the highest CPLs in legal marketing ($100–$600+).</p>
      <p><strong>Drivers / barriers:</strong> Drivers — attorneys' persistent appetite for case volume, premium pricing for exclusivity, and an 8-year accident-data moat. Barriers — Google Ads cost/policy volatility, TCPA / FTC lead-gen scrutiny, state-bar advertising rules, crowded competitor field.</p>
      <p><strong>Peer benchmarks:</strong> Quintessa Marketing (large-scale, human-prescreened MVA retainers); On Point Legal Leads (exclusive MVA leads, founded ~2016); 4LegalLeads (~20-year-old exclusive auto-injury provider). Marketing-agency M&amp;A comps: generally 4x–8x EBITDA; only &gt;20%-margin, low-concentration, high-retention agencies reach 8x–12x. This target's 8.1% disclosed margin sits well below that premium tier, making the 8.60x ask hard to justify.</p>
    </section>

